name: NSError.UserInfoKey
desc: These keys may exist in the user info dictionary.

items.name: let NSURLErrorKey: String
items.desc: The corresponding value is an NSURL object.

items.name: let NSFilePathErrorKey: String
items.desc: Contains the file path of the error.

items.name: let NSHelpAnchorErrorKey: String
items.desc: The corresponding value is an NSString containing the localized help corresponding to the help button. See helpAnchor for more information.

items.name: let NSLocalizedDescriptionKey: String
items.desc: The corresponding value is a localized string representation of the error that, if present, will be returned by localizedDescription.

items.name: let NSLocalizedFailureReasonErrorKey: String
items.desc: The corresponding value is a localized string representation containing the reason for the failure that, if present, will be returned by localizedFailureReason.

items.name: let NSLocalizedRecoveryOptionsErrorKey: String
items.desc: The corresponding value is an array containing the localized titles of buttons appropriate for displaying in an alert panel.

items.name: let NSLocalizedRecoverySuggestionErrorKey: String
items.desc: The corresponding value is a string containing the localized recovery suggestion for the error.

items.name: let NSRecoveryAttempterErrorKey: String
items.desc: The corresponding value is an object that conforms to the NSErrorRecoveryAttempting informal protocol.

items.name: let NSStringEncodingErrorKey: String
items.desc: The corresponding value is an NSNumber object containing the NSStringEncoding value.

items.name: let NSUnderlyingErrorKey: String
items.desc: The corresponding value is an error that was encountered in an underlying implementation and caused the error that the receiver represents to occur.

items.name: static func != (ErrorUserInfoKey, ErrorUserInfoKey) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether two values are not equal.
